I was having the same problem and I think it&#39;s related to this: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/issues/2327

It has something to do with jackson deserialization, you can find more info here: https://www.baeldung.com/jackson-object-mapper-tutorial#2-creating-custom-serializer-or-deserializer

I solved it by creating a custom mapper that enables the MapperFeature.USE_STD_BEAN_NAMING feature, something like this:


    @Configuration
    public class MapperConfig {

    	@Bean
    	public ObjectMapper jacksonObjectMapper() {
    		return new ObjectMapper().setPropertyNamingStrategy(propertyNamingStrategy()).enable(MapperFeature.USE_STD_BEAN_NAMING);
    	}
    }

Hope it helps you find a solution ;)

